# Documentation (`docs/`)

- Keep documentation in **`docs/`**. Large topics — **separate files** in thematic subfolders (e.g. `docs/architecture/`, `docs/api/`, `docs/deployment/`).
- **No monoliths**: split into logical files and cross-link.
- Maintain a **map** at `docs/` root — a file listing sections and links (name by project choice: `INDEX.md`, `README.md`, or `map.md`).
- If **`docs/skills-index.md`** (Cursor skills registry) exists — include a **link** in the docs map.
- New file in `docs/` — **update the map**. Path/module/structure changes — see **Code map and rules** (`code-map-and-rules.mdc`).
